# Known-good DEPLOYED binary baseline for `west darling-doctor` check 3.
#
# These are the md5s of the last-known-good deployed closure binaries in the install prefix. The
# doctor compares the deployed dyld (both copies) / mldr / darlingserver against these by default.
#
# Format: one "key = md5" per line; '#' comments. Keys: dyld, mldr, dserver.
# UPDATE this file (and note why + which Bead) whenever a legitimate rebuild changes what is
# deployed — otherwise the doctor will (correctly) flag the new deploy as a baseline mismatch.
#
# Current baseline (2026-07-04, task #116 A0-ARCH stage 2a): darlingserver updated to the
# A0-ARCH stage 2a landing (shadow MicroState machine: one per-thread run-state written by
# a single legality-asserting transition function at every _running/_suspended flip site,
# 32-entry per-thread transition tape dumped on violations and from the duct-tape panic
# funnel; DSERVER_MSTATE_ABORT=1 gate wiring; branch fix/a0-arch-redesign, see
# tests/A0-ARCH-STAGE2.md). Acceptance: quick gate 15/15 gating green (synth 13/13 +
# brew xz 2/2 strict) with ZERO mstate violations across the battery incl. brew; fuzz
# survival 4/6 RED identical to stage-1c (deaths = pre-existing classes, tape-verified);
# perf A/B no regression (nestwait 3642/3614/3692 vs ~3635-3679, 300xtrue 2s identical);
# ASAN leg green on 9/9 gating legs (needs ASAN_OPTIONS=detect_stack_use_after_return=0,
# fake-stack vs fiber switches). dyld/mldr unchanged.
#   dyld    79b22273  (dyld-733.6, boot-compatible with the deployed 06-15 closure)
#   mldr    f0cd2a82  (perf#21b compact-fd band)
#   dserver e50a3450  (ring + A0 a3de8c2 + A0-ARCH stages 0/1 + 2a shadow machine)
# Previous dserver baseline: a889e85f (stage 1, backup darlingserver.a889e85f.bak in
# darling-prefix/bin and job tmp); before that 886d13af (a3de8c2, task #113).

dyld    = 79b22273481ea61ab63c0606c23ab300
mldr    = f0cd2a82efc4cb4614b63cabac0168f8
dserver = e50a3450b3543621711359c754a9d7e1
